Flood Phase in Counties

Marcela

11/10/2019


Subsetting by Affected Counties and Flood Phase

4086 tweets sent during the disaster were filtered based on the 9 counties affected in the disaster –according to the reports: Arapahoe, Boulder, Denver, El Paso, Jefferson, Larimer, Logan, Morgan and Weld.

From the 2804 tweets resulting from this process, only 849 tweets sent during the “Flood” stage were filtered for content analysis.

Most common words (Within Affected Counties)

A quick view of the most common words in the whole dataset:

##  9 colorado        54
## 10 rt              54
## # … with 2,160 more rows

Again, since “boulder” is the most common word and is going to have a big effect in our topic modelling, it was removed from the dataset. The following five terms (“boulderflood”, “coflood”, “cowx”, “amp”, “|”) were also excluded because they were so common and used neutrally in all four stages. After excluding these six terms, the new list of common words looks as follows:
